is Haji Abu Bakar's older sister.</Para><Para>"It was not easy because we had to pull together our family members to console my mother and try to find out more information," said the 47-year-old. "It was very sudden. We are all very devastated by the news."</Para><Para>Ms Amilia described her uncle as loving.</Para><Para>"He was very wise with his words and consoled me through many troubling times," she said, adding that he often did charitable work for religious causes with her mother. ST_20180321_VNBUSXY4IA_3850525.jpg Related StorySingaporean pilgrim dies in Mecca bus accident</Para><Para>Haji Abu Bakar's granddaughter, who wanted to be identified only as Ms Aishah, said he was always concerned about his family's religious education.</Para><Para>"He would always teach his children and grandchildren about our culture and religion," said the 21-year-old.</Para><Para>Ms Amilia said her uncle would organise weekly prayer sessions in his office for the Muslim community.</Para><Para>Haji Abu Bakar's three children left Singapore for Saudi Arabia on Wednesday for the burial.</Para><Para>His wife was warded in the intensive care unit of King Faisal Hospital with two other passengers. Ten others were reported to be at another hospital, while 17 had been discharged. An update on the current condition of those injured is not available.</Para><Para>A spokesman for the travel agency said it has been organising pilgrimages about two or three times a year since it began operations in 2002 and regularly charters buses from the bus operator.</Para><Para>This was the first accident the agency had encountered, he added.</Para><Para>He said that a private prayer session for the family, friends and employees of Haji Abu Bakar was held on Wednesday evening.</Para><Para>In a post on its Facebook page, Abu Bakar Travel Services thanked well-wishers for their condolences on the death of its director.</Para><Para>"Together we pray for the well-being and recovery of Hajah Fauziah Alias and all the other pilgrims," the agency added.</Para></TailParas><Byline fid="by" index="field">Zhaki Abdullah,Kimberley Chia </Byline><Credit fid="cr" index="field"></Credit><Contact fid="ct" index="field"></Contact><Notes fid="rf" index="field"></Notes><Art fid="art" index="field"></Art><Copyright fid="cy" index="field">(c) 2018 Singapore Press Holdings Limited </Copyright></Article></ArchiveDoc><AdocTOC adoctype="article"><Item size="0" ref="distdoc:archive/ArchiveDoc::Article" type="arttext"></Item><Item size="0" ref="distdoc:archive/InvertText" type="invtext"></Item></AdocTOC></DistDoc>

